subsection.p:
	Sometimes it is so important that the inverse be a function that we are willing to sacrifice part of the original function to achieve this result.  Look again at the graph of F(x)=x^2 - 4. If we use only nonnegative x-values for the domain, we create a new function,
f(x)=x^2 - 4,~~x \ge 0
shown below.


        function and inverse function


        \tikzset{%
        }
